        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 3:13PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 313 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 3
miles northeast of Deerfield Reservoir, or 12 miles northwest of Hill
City, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Flag Mountain, Mystic, and Deerfield Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
